27. Negative tests.
- The postprocessor expression must reference the index column
- The postprocessor expression must be a function, not an identifier
- The postprocessor expression must return String
- The postprocessor must not contain non-deterministic functions
- The postprocessor must not contain arrayJoin
- A postprocessor that produces a token containing separator characters throws BAD_ARGUMENTS at query time
28. ngrams tokenizer + postprocessor: postprocessed tokens are not re-tokenized.
